HEADWORD: Ecclesiastic
<hw>Ec*cle`si*as"tic</hw> <pr>(?; 277)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>ecclesiasticus</ets>, Gr. <?/, fr. <?/ an assembly of citizens
called out by the crier; also, the church, fr. <?/ called out, fr. <?/
to call out; <grk>'ek</grk> out + <?/ to call. See <er>Ex-</er>, and
<er>Hale</er>, <pos>v. t.</pos>, <er>Haul</er>.]</ety> <def>Of or
pertaining to the church. See <er>Ecclesiastical</er>.</def>
⟦ldquo⟧<xex>Ecclesiastic</xex> government.⟦rdquo⟧
<rj><au>Swift.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

